</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="11D265234544B646B595FE96FE9A1FD1" pageId="7" pageNumber="466" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="597736A84544B646B595FE96FAEA1C1D" blockId="7.[151,1437,150,681]" pageId="7" pageNumber="466">
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA4544B646B595FE96FE801C65" bold="true" box="[199,317,259,285]" pageId="7" pageNumber="466">Remarks:</emphasis>
The determination of materials listed by 
<bibRefCitation id="3D594B594544B646B7A9FE96FC4A1C65" author="Dziedzielewicz, J." box="[763,1015,259,285]" pageId="7" pageNumber="466" pagination="42 - 45" refId="ref14019" refString="Dziedzielewicz, J. (1914) O owadzie Posniezku (Boreus), zyjacym na ziemiach Polski. Kosmos, 29 (1 - 3), 42 - 45." type="journal article" year="1914">Dziędzielewicz (1914)</bibRefCitation>
was confirmed by František Klapálek. All records mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="3D594B594544B646B4EEFEB2FDCA1C39" author="Svensson, S. A." box="[444,631,295,321]" pageId="7" pageNumber="466" pagination="26 - 32" refId="ref16833" refString="Svensson, S. A. (1972) Boreus Latreille, 1825 (Mecoptera). A Synopsis of Described Species. Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution, 3 (1), 26 - 32. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187631272 X 00049" type="journal article" year="1972">Svensson (1972)</bibRefCitation>
are based on the summarized publication of 
<bibRefCitation id="3D594B594544B646B13CFEB2FAD01C39" author="Dziedzielewicz, J." box="[1134,1389,295,321]" pageId="7" pageNumber="466" pagination="38 - 40" refId="ref14051" refString="Dziedzielewicz, J. (1918) Owady siatkoskrzydlowate ziem Polski (Insecta neuropteroidea Poloniae terrarum). Rozprawy i Wiadomo s ci z Muzeum im. Dzieduszyckich, Lwow, 4 (1 - 4), 38 - 40." type="journal article" year="1918">Dziędzielewicz (1918)</bibRefCitation>
and listed under 
<collectingCountry id="21DF76384544B646B470FEDEFECE1C1D" box="[290,371,331,357]" name="Poland" pageId="7" pageNumber="466">Poland</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="3D594B594544B646B42FFEDEFDA81C1D" author="Penny, N. D." box="[381,533,331,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="466" pagination="141 - 217" refId="ref16477" refString="Penny, N. D. (1977) A systematic study of the family Boreidae (Mecoptera). The University of Kansas science bulletin, 51, 141 - 217." type="journal article" year="1977">Penny (1977)</bibRefCitation>
did not report this species from 
<collectingCountry id="21DF76384544B646B6D2FEDEFC671C1D" box="[896,986,331,357]" name="Ukraine" pageId="7" pageNumber="466">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
on published distributional maps.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="597736A84544B646B595FEFAFCDE1CA9" blockId="7.[151,1437,150,681]" pageId="7" pageNumber="466">
<bibRefCitation id="3D594B594544B646B595FEFAFE191CF1" author="Fudakowski, J." box="[199,420,367,393]" pageId="7" pageNumber="466" pagination="202 - 204" refId="ref14390" refString="Fudakowski, J. (1923) Znane i nowe stanowiska Borens hiemalis L. i B. westwoodi Hag. (Neuropteroidea - Mecoptera). (Neue und bekannte Standorte von Boreus hiemalis L. u. B. westwoodi Hag. in Polen). Polskie Pismo Entomologiczne, 2 (4), 202 - 204." type="journal article" year="1923">Fudakowski (1923)</bibRefCitation>
reported two additional localities of this species, one from the Tatra Mountains and the second from the western part of the Roztochchya Region within the current territory of 
<collectingCountry id="21DF76384544B646B127FE06FB7B1CD5" box="[1141,1222,403,429]" name="Poland" pageId="7" pageNumber="466">Poland</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName id="9EC84D2B4544B646B183FE06FADA1CD5" authorityName="Hagen" authorityYear="1866" box="[1233,1383,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Boreidae" genus="Boreus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="466" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="westwoodi">
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA4544B646B183FE06FADA1CD5" box="[1233,1383,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="466">B. westwoodi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also occurs in the eastern part of Roztochchya belonging to 
<collectingCountry id="21DF76384544B646B653FE22FCE21CA9" box="[769,863,439,465]" name="Ukraine" pageId="7" pageNumber="466">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="597736A84544B646B595FE4EFE9A1FD1" blockId="7.[151,1437,150,681]" pageId="7" pageNumber="466">
Distributional data reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="3D594B594544B646B775FE4EFD471C8D" author="Rizun, V. B. &amp; Konovalova, I. B. &amp; Yanytskyi, T. P." box="[551,762,475,501]" pageId="7" pageNumber="466" refId="ref16637" refString="Rizun, V. B., Konovalova, I. B. &amp; Yanytskyi, T. P. (2000) Ridkisni i znykayuchi vydy komakh v entomolohichnykh kolektsiyakh Derzhavnoho pryrodoznavchoho muzeyu. [Rare and endangered insect species of Ukraine in the entomological collections of the State Museum of Natural History]. SMNH, Lviv, 71 pp. [in Ukrainian, English summary]" type="book" year="2000">
Rizun 
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA4544B646B722FE4EFD141C8D" box="[624,681,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="466">et al.</emphasis>
(2000)
</bibRefCitation>
are based on faunistical information published in Red Book of 
<collectingCountry id="21DF76384544B646B5EBFE6AFEAE1F61" box="[185,275,511,537]" name="Ukraine" pageId="7" pageNumber="466">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
(1994), and results of SMNH collection determination; altogether 
<specimenCount id="4FCEFD214544B646B14EFE6AFB661F61" box="[1052,1243,511,537]" pageId="7" pageNumber="466" type="generic">seven specimens</specimenCount>
were mentioned (see also above): (1) Chornohora (catalogue number 
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA4544B646B7A9FDB6FC0C1F45" box="[763,945,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="466">Е 21.02.01.01/7</emphasis>
); (2) Kozmeshchyk (
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA4544B646B1F8FDB6FAF91F45" box="[1194,1348,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="466">21.02.01.01/5</emphasis>
); (3–5) Foreshchynka (
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA4544B646B417FDD2FE441F19" box="[325,505,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="466">Е 21.02.01.01/2</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA4544B646B75AFDD2FD011F19" box="[520,700,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="466">Е 21.02.01.01/3</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA4544B646B7A6FDD2FC1A1F19" box="[756,935,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="466">Е 21.02.01.01/4</emphasis>
); (6) Turkul (
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA4544B646B117FDD2FB441F19" box="[1093,1273,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="466">Е 21.02.01.01/1</emphasis>
) [collected by J. Dziędzielewicz and H. Huppenthal]; (7) Nesamovyte (
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA4544B646B671FDFEFC641FFC" box="[803,985,618,644]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="466">Е 21.02.01.01/6</emphasis>
) [collected by an anonymous author in 
<date id="2D7610684544B646B5C5FD1BFEA11FD1" box="[151,284,654,681]" pageId="7" pageNumber="466" value="1924-09-15">15.IX.1924</date>
].
</paragraph>
